{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FXokgyM5w9vEMho7BzueFP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## lopdf 0.31.0 Rust Crate API Reference\n\nBased on my direct examination of the source files in `~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/lopdf-0.31.0/src/`, here are the answers to your questions:\n\n### 1. Methods to Merge/Combine Multiple Documents\n\n**There is NO built-in \"merge\" method in Document.** The library provides lower-level utilities you combine manually:\n\n- **`renumber_objects_with(starting_id: u32)`** (processor.rs:165) — Renumber all objects starting from a given ID. This is critical when combining documents to avoid ID conflicts.\n- **Direct object manipulation**: You manually collect objects from multiple documents into a single `Document.objects` BTreeMap\n- **`doc.objects.extend(other_doc.objects)`** — Extend the objects map (shown in merge.rs example)\n- **`Xref.merge(&mut self, xref: Xref)`** (xref.rs:59) — Merge cross-reference tables (only for low-level use)\n\nThe merge.rs example shows the full pattern: collect pages and objects from each document, renumber them with renumber_objects_with(), handle catalog/pages merging manually, then combine into the main document.\n\n### 2. What Document::save Returns\n\n**`Result<File>`** — not `Result<(), Error>`\n\nFrom writer.rs:13:\n```rust\npub fn save<P: AsRef<Path>>(&mut self, path: P) -> Result<File>\n```\n\nThere's also:\n```rust\npub fn save_to<W: Write>(&mut self, target: &mut W) -> Result<()>\n```\n\nSo save() returns the File handle, while save_to() returns ().\n\n### 3. Document::renumber_objects_with — YES, EXISTS\n\n**Signature** (processor.rs:165):\n```rust\npub fn renumber_objects_with(&mut self, starting_id: u32)\n```\n\nTakes a mutable self and a u32 starting ID. There's also a convenience method:\n```rust\npub fn renumber_objects(&mut self)  // calls renumber_objects_with(1)\n```\n\n### 4. How to Access the Pages Tree\n\nAccess via the **catalog**:\n\n```rust\npub fn catalog(&self) -> Result<&Dictionary>\npub fn catalog_mut(&mut self) -> Result<&mut Dictionary>\n```\n\nThen get the Pages reference from the catalog and dereference with `get_object_mut`:\n\nFrom document.rs, pages are accessed through the catalog's \"Pages\" reference:\n```rust\npub fn get_pages(&self) -> BTreeMap<u32, ObjectId>\npub fn page_iter(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = ObjectId>\npub fn get_object_mut(&mut self, id: ObjectId) -> Result<&mut Object>\n```\n\nPattern from the merge example:\n```rust\nlet pages = doc.get_pages();  // Returns BTreeMap<u32, ObjectId>\n// OR\ndoc.catalog_mut()?  // Get catalog dict\n    .get_mut(b\"Pages\")?  // Get Pages reference\n```\n\n### 5. Document.is_encrypted — PUBLIC METHOD\n\n**is_encrypted() is a public method, NOT a field**\n\nFrom document.rs:253:\n```rust\npub fn is_encrypted(&self) -> bool {\n    self.get_encrypted().is_ok()\n}\n```\n\nIt's a method that checks if the trailer contains an \"Encrypt\" entry. There's also:\n```rust\npub fn get_encrypted(&self) -> Result<&Dictionary>  // Returns the encryption dict\npub fn decrypt<P: AsRef<[u8]>>(&mut self, password: P) -> Result<()>  // Decrypt the document\n```\n\n---\n\n**Additional useful methods for document construction:**\n- `new()` / `with_version(version)` — Create documents\n- `new_object_id()` — Generate IDs without adding objects\n- `add_object<T: Into<Object>>(object: T) -> ObjectId` — Add objects and get their ID\n- `get_object_mut(id)` — Get mutable reference to object (automatically dereferences)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6e5030e32a6fdfd5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 103145\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 48134</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b32962c-f496-4079-9ef0-4b12af617e35","uuid":"8228148d-6aac-492d-94d8-1a41d4350bf5","tool_use_result"