{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NhnP3myjnzqjMv7LRUe92g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the correct lopdf API. Let me implement the merge function properly:\n\n1. `renumber_objects_with(starting_id: u32)` exists\n2. `save()` returns `Result<File>`, but `save_to(&mut writer)` returns `Result<()>`\n3. `is_encrypted()` is a method\n4. Need to manually copy objects and build pages tree\n\nLet me implement the merge properly. The key pattern is:\n1. Load all documents, checking if any are encrypted\n2. Renumber each document's objects to avoid conflicts\n3. Collect all objects\n4. Build the final pages tree\n\nHere's the plan:\n\n\n1. Create a new empty Document\n2. For each source doc: renumber its objects, copy all objects to result, collect page IDs\n3. Create a new Pages tree combining all page IDs\n4. Save\n\nThe tricky part is handling the /Parent references in pages—each source page points back to its original pages dictionary. Rather than trying to update all those references, I'll renumber each source document's objects with an offset, collect all the objects into the target, then build a fresh pages tree that properly links everything together.\n\nNow I'm writing the Rust implementation to load the documents...\n\nFinishing the merge function...\n\nI need to make sure the file creation handles missing parent directories properly—if the output path's parent doesn't exist, `File::create` will fail with an IO error, which is what the test expects. Let me verify that `Document::save_to` properly propagates those errors. Writing the merge logic... Setting up the PDF catalog and trailer...\n\nActually, I'm realizing there's a potential issue with how the pages tree gets reconstructed when merging source documents. Each source document has its own pages tree structure with a root /Pages object that contains /Kids, but when I'm extracting and recombining them, I need to make