{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QFHSk4fzknZVpVSbcExNRs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→name: Release\n     2→\n     3→on:\n     4→  push:\n     5→    tags:\n     6→      - 'v*'\n     7→\n     8→permissions:\n     9→  contents: write\n    10→\n    11→jobs:\n    12→  build:\n    13→    strategy:\n    14→      matrix:\n    15→        include:\n    16→          - target: aarch64-apple-darwin\n    17→            os: macos-14\n    18→          - target: x86_64-apple-darwin\n    19→            os: macos-13\n    20→          - target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\n    21→            os: ubuntu-22.04\n    22→          - target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n    23→            os: ubuntu-22.04\n    24→            use_cross: true\n    25→\n    26→    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n    27→    steps:\n    28→      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n    29→\n    30→      - uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable\n    31→        with:\n    32→          targets: ${{ matrix.target }}\n    33→\n    34→      - uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2\n    35→        with:\n    36→          key: ${{ matrix.target }}\n    37→\n    38→      - name: Install cross\n    39→        if: matrix.use_cross\n    40→        uses: taiki-e/install-action@cross\n    41→\n    42→      - name: Build (native)\n    43→        if: '!matrix.use_cross'\n    44→        run: cargo build --release --target ${{ matrix.target }} -p ezpdf-cli\n    45→\n    46→      - name: Build (cross)\n    47→        if: matrix.use_cross\n    48→        run: cross build --release --target ${{ matrix.target }} -p ezpdf-cli\n    49→\n    50→      - name: Strip binary (Linux/macOS)\n    51→        run: strip target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/ezpdf || true\n    52→\n    53→      - name: Package binary\n    54→        run: |\n    55→          BINARY=target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/ezpdf\n    56→          ARCHIVE=ezpdf-${{ github.ref_name }}-${{ matrix.target }}.tar.gz\n    57→          tar czf \"$ARCHIVE\" -C \"$(dirname \"$BINARY\")\" \"$(basename \"$BINARY\")\"\n    58→          echo \"ARCHIVE=$ARCHIVE\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n    59→\n    60→      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n    61→        with:\n    62→          name: ezpdf-${{ matrix.target }}\n    63→          path: ${{ env.ARCHIVE }}\n    64→\n    65→  release:\n    66→    needs: build\n    67→    runs-on: ubuntu-22.04\n    68→    steps:\n    69→      - uses: actions/download-artifact@v4\n    70→        with:\n    71→          merge-multiple: true\n    72→          path: artifacts/\n    73→\n    74→      - uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v2\n    75→        with:\n    76→          files: artifacts/*.tar.gz\n    77→          generate_release_notes: true\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b32962c-f496-4079-9ef0-4b12af617e35","uuid":"c8808300-864d-4045-b39a-fd21ec03da19","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/enzhou/Projects/ez-pdf/.github/workflows/release.yml","content":"name: Release\n\non:\n  push:\n    tags:\n      - 'v*'\n\npermissions:\n  contents: write\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        include:\n          - target: aarch64-apple-darwin\n            os: macos-14\n          - target: x86_64-apple-darwin\n            os: macos-13\n          - target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            os: ubuntu-22.04\n          - target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            os: ubuntu-22.04\n            use_cross: true\n\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable\n        with:\n          targets: ${{ matrix.target }}\n\n      - uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2\n        with:\n          key: ${{ matrix.target }}\n\n      - name: Install cross\n        if: matrix.use_cross\n        uses: taiki-e/install-action@cross\n\n      - name: Build (native)\n        if: '!matrix.use_cross'\n        run: cargo build --release --target ${{ matrix.target }} -p ezpdf-cli\n\n      - name: Build (cross)\n        if: matrix.use_cross\n        run: cross build --release --target ${{ matrix.target }} -p ezpdf-cli\n\n      - name: Strip binary (Linux/macOS)\n        run: strip target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/ezpdf || true\n\n      - name: Package binary\n        run: |\n          BINARY=target/${{ matrix.target }}/release/ezpdf\n          ARCHIVE=ezpdf-${{ github.ref_name }}-${{ matrix.target }}.tar.gz\n          tar czf \"$ARCHIVE\" -C \"$(dirname \"$BINARY\")\" \"$(basename \"$BINARY\")\"\n          echo \"ARCHIVE=$ARCHIVE\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n\n      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: ezpdf-${{ matrix.target }}\n          path: ${{ env.ARCHIVE }}\n\n  release:\n    needs: build\n    runs-on: ubuntu-22.04\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/download-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          merge-multiple: true\n          path: artifacts/\n\n      - uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v2\n        with:\n          files: artifacts/*.tar.gz\n          generate_release_notes: true\n","numLines":78,"startLine":1,"totalLines":78}}}
